August 30 at 11:33 AM ·

CVE Parents: We are so excited to be back IN PERSON tomorrow, Monday, August 31st.

A few reminders:
1. Please send chrome books and chargers back to school with your student as they use them daily in their classrooms.
2. All students will report to the cafeteria to grab breakfast and then head to the classrooms.
3. Masks are still required for 4th & 5th graders and on buses.
4. Teachers will be passing out neck gaiters to every student tomorrow as well.
5. SLAM also starts after school tomorrow. Please make sure your child’s teacher or the office knows your child is to attend.

Finally, thanks for helping make the past 7 days of distance learning a success! The decision to move to distance learning was NOT an easy decision, but as always, the safety of our students and staff is our number 1 priority! We can’t wait to see our kiddos tomorrow!!

post_text:
Parents,

Hello Caney Valley,

I just wanted to give our parents an update of our virtual start. At the High School we had 40% of our students not check in with their teachers yesterday. The Middle School had 50%. Those students have been counted absent. Those absences will add up and turn into NC's (no credit) if they are not addressed. It will also turn into eligibility issues as well. It's not too late to get those absences turned into present. All you need to do is contact your teacher or turn in your assignments. Some teachers are hosting virtual meetings and recording them. If you can't participate live they are posting the records for you to view at a later time.

We know some students don't have access to the internet. If this is the case for you please contact the MS or HS so we can get a packet prepared for you.

Sincerely,

Caney Valley Schools

Kelli Hembree Longan
August 20 at 10:32 AM ·

Update: If you are coming to pickup after 3:00, please call the office at 918.535.2205 and pull into the bus loop. I will run it all out to you! I will be here until 4:00. If you can’t make it by then, please contact your child’s teacher to make arrangements for later pickup.

CVE Parents:

We will begin distributing materials for all students PreK-5th grade around 10:45 this morning. We have attempted to put all siblings together for ease of pick up. Parents picking up materials for students in 2nd through 5th grade will utilize the car loop. Parents picking up materials for students in PreK through 1st will use the bus loop. If you have children in both pickup lines, all materials will be picked up with the older student's grade in the car loop. Please write your child's name on a piece of paper and have it posted in the window. We will try to make this process as smooth as possible, but please be patient with us!

8/19/2020

Dear Caney Valley parents, staff and community members:

Today, we received notification that a Caney Valley employee has tested positive for COVID-19. While we must protect the privacy of the person involved, we believe it is best to communicate transparently with you so you can make well-informed decisions for your family.

There is nothing more important to Caney Valley School District than the safety and health of our students, our staff and their families. All students at Caney Valley Elementary could have had close contact with the teacher, so we will be closing on-site instruction and will utilize our remote learning platform from August 20th to August 28th.

We are working…

I want to thank our Administration Team and staff for all of their work to make today a success. Parents, thank you for being patient as we begin this new phase of instruction.
Things are changing daily, as expected. For our virtual students and parents, due to the number of students who are taking advantage of the virtual… More

post_text:
Today after many years of teaching at Caney Valley Bob and Janae Taylor are retiring. They have touched so many lives during the years here at Caney Valley! If you have a photo or a memory you would like to share please email kirktaylor87@gmail.com
Bob and Janae congratulations on your retirement and the next chapter in your lives. You will both be missed by your Caney Valley family!! ❤️🖤❤️🖤
shared_text:
Janae Taylor
July 23 at 8:51 AM ·

After 52 years at Caney Valley Public Schools (12 years attending 1st-12th grades and 40 years as a teacher and coach) Coach Taylor is driving away from Caney Valley one last time. I am retiring with him after 21 years at CVE and a total of 30 years teaching. Our hearts are filled with great memories, funny moments, difficult dilemmas (all teachers have them), and most of all an abundance of friends and acquaintances. Thanks for letting us be a part of your family’s life. As Coach Taylor says “We will see you at Walmart!”
I am always proud when a voice says “There’s Coach Taylor!” or a past student comes and shakes his hand.

We, his family, would love to give Coach Taylor a box of memories. If you would like to share a memory, a favorite game, pictures of then and now, or any special words please comment here or email kirktaylor87@gmail.com
Thanks

post_text: I just want to take a second and say I LOVE being a Caney Valley Trojan! CV not only has amazing teachers and staff but we have a great community!! If there is ever a need in our classrooms our great community is always there to help! Our 1st grade teachers asked for some headphones for their students to use with their Chromebooks this year and within 6 hours all 3 classrooms have been fully supplied with the headphones they needed. We also had another parent come up with an idea for partitions for classrooms that use tables. DONE! They are being made for Pre-K, K, 1st, Math and Reading Specialist, Library and the Elementary Secretary. ￼Thank you to everyone that has been a part of making going back to school that much safer! We love you Trojan Country!!! ❤️🖤❤️🖤

shared_text:
Caney Valley School District
June 30 at 7:25 PM ·

With graduation quickly approaching we wanted to give an update everyone on our plans. Our in person graduation for 2020 seniors will be at the football field at 10 AM on July 18th. We ask anyone not feeling well to please not attend. The program will be recorded and posted to the school website and posted to facebook. We are going to ask everyone to please practice social distancing. Masks are strongly encouraged. Every other bleacher will be marked off, but you are welcome to utilize the visitors' bleachers or use lawn chairs on the track. We will have hand sanitizer available. Bathrooms will be available for emergency use only.

If you have any questions please contact Travis Lashbrook at TLashbrook@caneyvalleyschool.org or by calling (918) 536-3425.

Sincerely,

Travis Lashbrook
Caney Valley High School Principal
TLashbrook@caneyvalleyschool.org
(918) 536-3425

We want to take a minute to welcome Dr. Cantrell and his family to our Caney Valley family and introduce him to everyone. The future looks bright for Caney Valley!!

Hello, to the communities of Ramona, Ochelata, Vera, and Oglesby. My name is Steve Cantrell, and I am proud to have been named as the next superintendent of the Caney Valley school system. I come from a long line of educators and grew up on my family’s small cattle farm that was originally my grandfather's. The cows and equipment from the Olin Lewis Dairy were sold, but my family kept some land and began raising beef cows. I graduated from Collinsville High School, where my father was an elementary principal for 42 years. In… More

post_text: Reminder for elementary parents. Please share this post and help us get the word out. Thank you!
shared_text:
Kelli Hembree Longan
May 27 at 12:39 PM ·

CVE Parents:

We have been working to get everything ready for tomorrow’s final pickup from 4-6pm. We will be handing out awards for all students. If you were unable to retrieve your child’s personal belongings, we have those ready to go as well! Please park in the parking lot and make your way to the gym entrance. The awards will be given out in the lobby. We have also set out all items that were in our Lost & Found to be claimed, and we will allow one parent to walk through to check it out! You are not required to go through lost & found if you do not choose to do so. Please note that after pickup, any unclaimed items will be boxed up and donated as we do every summer. We will also be limiting the inflow of traffic in our facility, so please only have one person come to retrieve these things. If you have a fourth grade student, we have a section set aside that is totally PE shoes that did not have names on them and were unable to be matched to the appropriate kiddo! So, if your 4th grade child is missing PE shoes, that’s the place to look!! Thanks for understanding!

post_text:
A Video Tribute to this year's Senior Class of 2020.
When you walked on campus last fall - FINALLY a Senior - you had no idea the challenges and disappointments that would come your way. We agree, it's not fair.
We cannot bring back your Senior Prom, Senior Day, your athletic season or give you more time in the halls of Caney Valley High School with your friends and favorite teachers. We know that you have worked so hard and waited your entire life for these moments.
This global pandemic makes us all appreciate the things we took for granted, However, when the dust settles you will be forever bound in an unforgettable way. Although it may look different this year, the message is the same......YOU MADE IT! Congrats Class of 2020. Our hats are off to you.

https://spark.adobe.com/video/5w4oXIGFusoaT

Students drop off and pick up

Monday May 18 –
9 to 11 a.m. (Middle school students only)
4 to 6 p.m. (all 6-12)

Tuesday May 19-
9 to 11 a.m. (High School students only)

If you can't make it or need to make different arrangements call for appointment

Rules to follow:
✅Bring something to carry your items.
✅Use social distancing guidelines.
✅If you see a friend or teacher please don't stop and talk.
✅Only one person at a time (don't come in a group/Parents let the students go in by themselves or if there is a health issue 1 person can go in for that student).
✅Try not to touch anything but your locker.
Lockers will be open to speed up the process.

1st stop Library steps to turn in…

post_text: This one needs no introduction! She is the fearless leader of CVE! Thank you Mrs. Longan for everything you do for our students and staff!! If you have any memories or comments you would like to share please leave them below. Thank you!
shared_text:
Virginia Fogle
May 9 at 9:41 AM ·

And last but not least a big thank you to our CVE leader. She has been working non stop since our educational venue has changed. She has worked with our staff to be sure our students would be able to continue their educational journey. Trying to be sure everyone was safe in picking up and dropping off student work, picking up their belongings and enrollment packets for next year was not an easy task. She has been at work everyday. Thank you Kelli Longan for everything you do for us and keeping us on track.

shared_text:
Kelli Hembree Longan is with Sandi Willcox and 8 others.
May 7 at 6:33 AM ·

These wonderful people are my teachers and assistants for 4th grade, 5th grade, and special education at CVE! They all help keep our upper elementary students learning and growing while preparing them for their next journey to middle school! Our district technology guru/after school SLAM director is also pictured! She works very hard to keep our chromebooks, classroom technology, ALL our online educational accounts and Internet going and then spends her afternoons providing homework help and activities for kids after school! We are so lucky to have these amazing people at CVE!

post_text: Reminder!! Call to make an appointment this week. Please share this to get the word out. Thank you!
shared_text:
Caney Valley School District
April 6 at 12:50 PM ·

2020-2021 Athletic Physicals

Athletic physicals will be the week of May 4-8, 2020. Every student participating in athletics for the 2020-2021 must have a physical completed by a doctor. Spring physicals will be given at Dr. Leatherman's office (previously Caney Valley Medical Clinic) in Ramona. Please call the clinic at 918-536-1024 to make an appointment. Students may go at any time during the week of May 4th with an appointment. Physicals will be $10 during that time period. After May 8th, physicals will be $40. Physical packets may be copied from the website or you may pick up a packet at Dr. Leatherman's office.

shared_text:
Caney Valley School District
April 13 at 8:35 PM ·

We are collecting photos of our seniors to honor them with a digital slideshow showcasing their accomplishments and achievements. We would like photos of our seniors in their prom dresses, caps and gowns, holding signs with their future plans, college choices, scholarships, awards and honors. To accomplish this, we need photos from our community. Please send them by email or share them via google drive to Jennifer Pinkerton at jpinkerton@caneyvalleyschool.org. Please share this post to get the word out. Thank you!

We need photos submitted by May 1st. Thank you!

A message from Mr. Lashbrook.

Any students that did packet work for High School course work can turn it in anytime between now and May 8th at the High School. There is a file cabinet by the gym lobby. All virtual school work should be completed by May 8th as well.

We are still waiting on locker clean out. If you have something you need please email Mr. Lashbrook at tlashbrook@caneyvalleyschool.org.

If you have not turned in your pre-enrollement form for next school please do that soon. The forms can be found on our school website.

We are working on a virtual awards assembly for academics as well as athletics. When we have more information we will make that available.

thank you,

Travis Lashbrook
Caney Valley High School Principal/AD/Transportation Director
tlashbrook@caneyvalleyschool.org
(918) 536-3425

post_text: Turn on channel 6 right now and watch for 2 of CV’s own do what they love right here on Main Street. Great job boys!!!
shared_text:
Tess Maune
April 27 at 5:05 PM ·

MAKING MAIN STREET THEIR MAIN STAGE: Y’all have to watch these two tear up the streets of Ramona! 12-year-old Kale Evans and 10-year-old Speck Gann have spent their time during the pandemic dancing putting on shows on the streets of their small town. They don’t need a big stage or crowd, they just need some Michael Jackson music, a speaker and some space. Folks driving by are even giving the boys tips for the entertainment
💵 because they are so fun to watch.

The two have been dancing for years, dance addicts, they say! They’ve taught themselves the moonwalk and all the moves Michael Jackson made famous. They put on a great show. You can find them dancing most afternoons and on Saturday nights in the heart of Ramona. But you can also catch them tonight at 7 on KOTV - News On 6 during our hourlong “Oklahoma Together” special!

That’s photojournalist extraordinaire Michael Blair working the camera... he and I had a blast working on this story and we think you’re gonna love it!!

We are collecting photos of our seniors to honor them with a digital slideshow showcasing their accomplishments and achievements. We would like photos of our seniors in their prom dresses, caps and gowns, holding signs with their future plans, college choices, scholarships, awards and honors. To accomplish this, we need photos from our community. Please send them by email or share them via google drive to Jennifer Pinkerton at jpinkerton@caneyvalleyschool.org. Please share this post to get the word out. Thank you!

We need photos submitted by May 1st. Thank you!

CVMS 7th Grade Geography for Fiddler's Class:

Students can access ALL materials online via Google Classroom (text, assignments, study guides, and tests). Students can work at their own pace. Each time they submit an online assignment, I will receive an email. A student/parent letter can be located on their STREAM page.

If needed, paper packets can be picked up at the MS today. You can take a picture of completed material and either email or text me a photo of each page. If you are unable to submit a photo and need to turn in the paper version of the assignments, they will need to be turned in by May 8th.

Email me if you have any questions.
dfiddler@caneyvalleyschool.org

Note: Students must login to their gmail account before thet try to access Google Classroom. Your child's email will look similar to mine in most cases. First initial, last name, last 2 digits of graduation year-- 25, followed by @caneyvalleyschool.org.

2020-2021 Athletic Physicals

Athletic physicals will be the week of May 4-8, 2020. Every student participating in athletics for the 2020-2021 must have a physical completed by a doctor. Spring physicals will be given at Dr. Leatherman's office (previously Caney Valley Medical Clinic) in Ramona. Please call the clinic at 918-536-1024 to make an appointment. Students may go at any time during the week of May 4th with an appointment. Physicals will be $10 during that time period. After May 8th, physicals will be $40. Physical packets may be copied from the website or you may pick up a packet at Dr. Leatherman's office.

Caney Valley Elementary parents:

A note about packet pickup on Monday, April 6

In order to expedite the pickup process and avoid unnecessary contact, please have a sign to hold up in your car window with the name and grade of your student(s). We will also try to return any prescription medications you have provided to the school for your child. At this time, we will not return any over-the-counter meds. Thank you to Sarah Reinke for suggesting this!

We miss our students terribly and hope to see them all again soon! Stay safe and take care!

Letter to Caney Valley School Parents/Guardians and Patrons:

Dear Trojan Family,
Yesterday, we were advised that Caney Valley students would not return to classrooms after April 6 for the remainder of this current chool year. This executive order came from the Oklahoma State Board of Education and applies to all districts throughout Oklahoma. Additionally, the state board charged each district to develop and implement continuous learning plans so that students could complete their studies at home. This decision was endorsed by State health and education officials and believed to be most effective way to control the spread of COVID-19.

text: Program guide for OETA.

post_text: Thank you OETA!
shared_text:
Oklahoma State Department of Education
March 26 at 3:22 PM ·

Exciting news! 🎉 We have partnered with OETA to provide in-home learning opportunities for students. The goal is to bring parents, students and teachers together with content and curriculum to meet educational needs while schools are closed due to coronavirus.

Beginning Monday, March 30, OETA will be adjusting its daytime schedule to provide curriculum-based programming for students over the air on its broadcast channel, OETA WORLD. Programs will include PBS favorites like NOVA, Nature, American Experience and PBS KIDS programming.

Programming changes to OETA WORLD will take place Monday through Friday from 6 a.m. until 6 p.m. until the end of the school year.

Teachers and parents are encouraged to visit OETA.tv/LearningAtHome to view an updated program schedule, OETA’s statewide channel list, curriculum and activities.

post_text:
Caney Valley Family,

FYI, our mandatory statewide school closure begins today Monday, March 23. In this school closure, all public schools are to follow the same directive from the State Department of Education that includes no instruction (including no worksheets, packets or virtual learning), no grading, no activities or athletics & no staff development.

CV Public Schools remains committed to the safety and wellbeing of its students and staff. Our meal distributions will run from 9:30-10:30 @ both campuses. We realize that there are many questions about important events for students and staff that are coming up soon. Please be patient as we will be working to create a FAQ document that will hopefully address most questions. Please continue to check our website and facebook page for updated information.

post_text:
March 19, 2020

Dear Caney Valley School Parents and Guardians;

In our continued effort to keep you advised, the staff has secured a waiver that will result in:
Caney Valley Schools will resume its food service program Monday, March 23, 2020. Hours of operation will be from 9:30 a.m. through 10:30 a.m., Monday – Friday through April 6, 2020. Caney Valley Elementary and the High/Middle School campuses will be designated as primary distribution sites.
Primarily, this will be a grab and go type of service. You will be able to receive both Breakfast and Lunch. If your student requires another means of distribution please contact the district’s food service coordinator, Regina Shivel, at (918) 536-1017.
are extraordinary times of which Oklahomans are no stranger to and without a doubt we will get through these challenging times together.

Stay healthy and safe,
J Michael McClaren, Superintendent

March 18, 2020

Dear Caney Valley Educational Community,

The Oklahoma State Board of Education met, taking action to close all Oklahoma schools from March 17 through April 6. This includes extracurricular activities.

Members of the Caney Valley Schools administration will meet to plan for the continuing service to our students during this time period. We will share information as soon as possible on meal service through our child nutrition program.

The Caney Valley School leader team is working with state leaders to stay current on the most recent developments pertaining to the COVID-19 outbreak. As our understanding of the virus changes, it is important for the community to remain calm…

March 17 at 8:53 AM ·

Help has arrived.... This is a post that a homeschooling mom has shared and made public. ❤

Ok, so LOTS of parents are suddenly home with their kiddos...

We have always home schooled after I was a classroom teacher for more than a decade, so I say WELCOME and let me help you.😉

A few things to remember, this is a PERFECT time to make memories with your children and learn things beyond "normal" math and reading.

This is a great time to really help your child dig in and spend hours doing or learning something that they love or are passionate about.

Don't forget that there are TONS of documentaries on the streaming services that they might enjoy and learn a lot from.

Here are links that I have…

post_text:
Caney Valley Public Schools is pleased to again be partnering with Total Wellness to offer FREE wellness exams & vaccinations.

This is your chance to have your ”free annual report” so please take advantage of this valuable opportunity and register for your appointment today.

Total Wellness accepts most major PPO Health Insurance plans now including Community Care. (Tribal insurance is not accepted).

There will be a gift card drawing with 25 or more participants district wide.

Date: Friday; January 24, 2020, 12:00pm-3:00pm.

Please click on this link to register:

https://core.totalwellnessok.com/public/event/7549
